name: unique identity card for persons with disabilities

benefits.criteria: Unique Identity Card for Persons with Disabilities shall be provided for all applicable for all schemes .

eligibility: As per eligibility criteria mentioned in central government’s The Rights of Persons with Disability Act 2016
requiredDocuments: Passport size photo, Aadhar card, ration card photocopy of medical certificate from specialised doctors, community certificate, signature/thumb impression

name: National Identity Card for persons with Disabilities

benefits.criteria: Identity Card for persons with disabilities

eligibility: Persons with more than 40% disability are eligible.(Visually Challenged, Hearing Impaired, Disabilities in legs and arms (Locomotor Disability) , Intelectual Disability Autism , Mentally Ill, Cerebral Palsy, Leprosy Cured
requiredDocuments: Passport size photo-4 nos , Aadhar card, Ration card photocopy, Medical certificate from Specialised Doctor confirms disability

name: Maintenance Grant for persons Mentally Retarded (Intellectual Disability).
eligibility: Persons suffering from more than 40% disability in Mentally Retardation . Also those who have not received physical disability allowance from revenue dept.
requiredDocuments: Application, Photocopy of Identity card and Disability Certificate given by the concern Govt. Doctors , Passport size photo, Aadhar card photocopy, certificate from village administrative officer stating that the person has not received benefits from other departments, Savings Banked Account, Ration card photocopy.

name: Maintenance Allowance for Persons affected by Muscular Dystrophy
eligibility: Persons suffering from more than 40% Muscle Dystrophy.Also those who have not received physical disability allowance from revenue dept.
requiredDocuments: Application, Photocopy of Identity card for disabled persons, Passport size photo, Aadhar card photocopy, Ration card photocopy, certificate from village administrative officer stating that the person has not received benefits from other departments, Savings Banked Account

name: Maintenance Allowance for Persons affected by Leprosy
eligibility: Persons suffering from more than 40% Leprosy. Also those who have not received physical disability allowance from revenue dept.
requiredDocuments: Application, Photocopy of Identity card for disabled persons, Passport size photo, Aadhar card photocopy, Ration card photocopy, certificate from village administrative officer stating that the person has not received benefits from other departments savings banked account, ration card photocopy.

name: Bank loan for self employment

benefits.criteria: Recommendation to the bank to grand loan upto Rs.75000.Atleast 1/3rd or maximum Rs.25000 subsidy shall be provided.

eligibility: Persons aged between 18 and 45.Visually challenged, disability in arms and legs ,hearing impaired, .Also the persons should not have borrowed from any other banks.
requiredDocuments: Application,Photocopy of Identity card for disabled persons, Passport size photo, Aadhar card photocopy, ration card photocopy, savings bank passbook.

name: High Support Need

benefits.criteria: Rs. 1000/- Per Month for Maintenace person

eligibility: Persons suffering from more than 60% for Metaly Retaired, with Cerebral Palsy, Mentaly Retaired with Autism Muscular Dystrophy, Spinal card affected person,   Also those who have received Rs. 2000/- for month  physical disability Maintenance grant allowance from District Differently Welfare office.
requiredDocuments: Application,Photocopy of Identity card for disabled persons, Passport size photo, Aadhar card photocopy, ration card photocopy, savings bank passbook.

name: Loan for self employment by district co-operative banks through National Handicapped Finance Development Corporation (NHFDC)

benefits.criteria: Loan application from Central Cooperative banks operating in that district or cooperative societies nearby or urban cooperative banks should be submitted. Should produce 1 guarantor for loans till Rs.25000. Should produce 2 guarantors for loans till Rs.50000.Should provide applicant’s property as a guarantee for loan amounts beyond Rs.50000.Loan shall be disbursed at 4% interest. For non defaulting repayers, the government shall subsidize the interest rate.

eligibility: Should not have received loans from any other banks. Age should not be less than 18 and no limit for maximum age.Parents of mentally retarded persons below 14 are eligible for the loan.
requiredDocuments: Application, Photocopy of Identity card for disabled persons, Passport size photo, Aadhar card photocopy, ration card photocopy, certificate from village administrative officer stating that the person has not received benefits from other departments, linked savings banked account, ration card photocopy.Cooperative societies’ membership certificate.

name: Bank loan for self employment of the physically challenged ,under Prime Minister Employment Generation Programme (PMEGP) . Should be applied online).

benefits.criteria: Amount within the range of Rs.25000 to Rs.25,00,000 shall be recommended to be disbursed by nationalised banks. Through District Industral Center 35% grant for physically challenged persons in rural areas, center 25% Subsidy for physically challenged persons in urban areas and additional 5% Subsidy through District Differently Abled Welfare Office, Tirunelveli District.

eligibility: Should not have received loans from any other banks. Age should not be less than 18 and no limit for maximum age.Disability groups are also eligible for self employment loan for banks.
requiredDocuments: Apart from application registered online, Photocopy of Identity card for disabled persons, Aadhar card photocopy, ration card photocopy, photograph of the notice of the scheme should be submitted to the General Manager, District Industrial Center ,Tirunelveli.

name: Bank loan under the scheme of Unemployed Youth Employment Generation Programme (UYEGP) (should be applied online).

benefits.criteria: Amount within the range of Rs.25000 to Rs.5,00,000 shall be recommended to be disbursed by nationalised banks. Through District Industrial Center 25% Subsidy for physically challenged persons by the DIC and additional 5% Subsidy through District Differently Abled Welfare Office, Tirunelveli District.

eligibility: 1)8th standard pass 2)Should not have obtained loan from any other bank 3)Age limit 18 to 45 years
requiredDocuments: Along with the application registered online, Photocopy of Identity card for disabled persons, Aadhar card photocopy, ration card photocopy, photograph of the notice of the scheme to be produced to General Manager, District Industrial Center , Tirunelveli.
